So we cannot mark the URL generation as always safe, but only when we are sure there won't be multiple query params. This is the case when there are none or only one constant parameter given. E.g. we know beforehand this will be safe: - path('route') - path('route', {'param': 'value'}) But the following may not: - path('route', var) - path('route', {'param': ['val1', 'val2'] }) // a sub-array - path('route', {'param1': 'value1', 'param2': 'value2'}) If param1 and param2 reference placeholder in the route, it would still be safe. But we don't know.
